Detailed Description

The section has a list of all the data structures which are used internally by the driver.

Typedef Documentation

typedef struct CAN_DriverMCB_t CAN_DriverMCB

CAN Master Control Block.

The structure describes the CAN Driver and is used to hold the relevant information with respect to the CAN module.

typedef struct CAN_HwCfg_t CAN_HwCfg

CAN Hardware Atrributes.

The structure is used to store the hardware specific configuration which is passed to each driver instance

typedef struct CAN_MessageObject_t CAN_MessageObject

CAN message object block.

The structure defines the message object

Enumeration Type Documentation

enum CAN_DCANIfRegNum_t

This enumeration defines the DCAN interface register numbers.

Enumerator
CAN_DCANIfRegNum_1 

DCAN interface register number 1 used for both read and write

CAN_DCANIfRegNum_2 

DCAN interface register number 2 used for both read and write

CAN_DCANIfRegNum_3 

DCAN interface register number 3 used only for read only

enum CAN_DCANIntrLineNum_t

Enumerates the values used to represent the DCAN interrupt lines.

Enumerator
CAN_DCANIntrLineNum_0 

DCAN interrupt line 0

CAN_DCANIntrLineNum_1 

DCAN interrupt line 1

enum CAN_DriverState_t

This enumeration defines the values used to represent the CAN driver state.

Enumerator
CAN_DriverState_UNINIT 

Can controller not initialized

CAN_DriverState_STARTED 

Can controller started

CAN_DriverState_STOPPED 

Can controller stopped

CAN_DriverState_SLEEP 

Can controller in sleep mode
